    "Id": "mechdef_taipan_TPN-89_reynolds",
    "Name": "Taipan TPN-89 'Reynolds'",
    "Details": "The Reynolds variant is a one-of-a-kind battlefield refit of a captured TPN-89, modified in 3074 by Captain Jann Reynolds of Reynold's Raiders after stripping the original MASC system and all factory weapons. A right-torso PPC serves as the primary weapon, delivering substantially heavier damage than the original Light PPCs at the cost of significant heat. Two left-torso Flamers provide close-range harassment capability alongside a center-torso Small Laser. The machine was destroyed along with its pilot in 3079 during a Word of Blake counterstrike.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Improved Jammer</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 0.98</color></b>\n\n<color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limits: Left Upper, Right Upper</color>",
    "Icon": "uixTxrIcon_taipan_3160"
  },
